## Traps (carried from round 4 + added)

- `pytest --timeout-method=signal` hangs on asyncio selector loops;
  use `--timeout-method=thread` (carried).
- Pyright false-positives on `kaizen.llm.*` imports in worktrees —
  the editable install resolves at runtime but pyright needs an
  explicit re-index. Non-blocking; ignore.
- Pre-commit auto-stash bug continues to hit. Documented workaround
  in `rules/git.md` § "Pre-Commit Hook Workarounds" — use
  `git -c core.hooksPath=/dev/null commit ...` with in-body note.
  Round-2 nexus agent hit this and used the documented path.
- Spawned agents sometimes write files outside their assigned
  worktree (to main repo paths). The kaizen round-1 agent did this;
  the round-2 agent also committed to main's branch ref instead of
  the worktree branch. The commits landed correctly; just note that
  `git worktree list` may not reflect ongoing agent activity in the
  worktree's branch ref.
- Signal-handler race on `_shutdown_hooks_fired` now defended with
  `threading.Lock` + flag reset in `start()`. If a future refactor
  replaces the lock with `asyncio.Lock`, signal handlers (which run
  on the main thread) will deadlock on the async lock — keep
  `threading.Lock`.
- 4-char fingerprint → 8-char was a cross-SDK parity fix. If ANY
  future DataFlow / kaizen / kailash-rs code emits a 4-char
  fingerprint, the audit join breaks. Grep for `hexdigest()[:4]` in
  redteam sweeps.

